{{Infobox glacier | child = | name = Astudillo Glacier | other_name = | photo = | photo_width = | photo_alt = | photo_caption = | map = Antarctica | map_width = | map_alt = | map_caption = Location of Astudillo Glacier in [[Antarctica]] | mark = Blue_pog.svg | type = | location = [[Graham Land]] | coordinates = {{coord|64|53|S|62|51|W|region:AQ|format=dms|display=inline}} | coords_ref = | area = | length = | width = | thickness = unknown | elevation_max = | elevation_min = | terminus = [[Paradise Harbor]] | status = unknown | embedded = }}
'''Astudillo Glacier''' ({{coord|64|53|S|62|51|W|type:glacier_region:AQ_source:GNIS|display=inline,title}}) is a small [[glacier]] flowing into [[Paradise Harbor]] between [[Leith Cove]] and [[Skontorp Cove]] on the [[Danco Coast]] of [[Graham Land]]. The glacier was surveyed by the [[Chilean Antarctic Expedition]] of 1950&ndash;51, which applied the name, probably after an expedition member.
==See also== * [[List of glaciers in the Antarctic]] * [[Glaciology]]
