'''Fauna Europaea''' is a database of the [[scientific name]]s and distribution of all living [[multicellular]] [[Europe]]an land and fresh-water animals. It serves as a standard taxonomic source for animal taxonomy within the [[Pan-European Species directories Infrastructure]] (PESI).<ref name="NCBI - Fauna Europaea – all European animal species on the web">{{cite journal|title=Fauna Europaea – all European animal species on the web| pmc=4206781 | pmid=25349527 | doi=10.3897/BDJ.2.e4034| issue=2| year=2014| journal=Biodivers Data J| page=e4034 | last1 = de Jong | first1 = Y | last2 = Verbeek | first2 = M | last3 = Michelsen | first3 = V | last4 = Bjørn Pde | first4 = P | last5 = Los | first5 = W | last6 = Steeman | first6 = F | last7 = Bailly | first7 = N | last8 = Basire | first8 = C | last9 = Chylarecki | first9 = P | last10 = Stloukal | first10 = E | last11 = Hagedorn | first11 = G | last12 = Wetzel | first12 = FT | last13 = Glöckler | first13 = F | last14 = Kroupa | first14 = A | last15 = Korb | first15 = G | last16 = Hoffmann | first16 = A | last17 = Häuser | first17 = C | last18 = Kohlbecker | first18 = A | last19 = Müller | first19 = A | last20 = Güntsch | first20 = A | last21 = Stoev | first21 = P | last22 = Penev | first22 = L}}</ref>
Its construction was initially funded by the [[European Council]] (2000–2004). The project was co-ordinated by the [[University of Amsterdam]] which launched the first version in 2004, after which the database was transferred to the [[Natural History Museum, Berlin|Natural History Museum Berlin]] in 2015.<ref name="NCBI - Fauna Europaea – all European animal species on the web"/>
