'''Franz Firbas''' (* June 4, 1902 in [[Prague]]; † February 19, 1964 in [[Göttingen]]) was a German botanist who taught at the [[University of Gottingen]].<ref>[http://www.tandfonline.com/doi/pdf/10.1080/00173139109427761 Presidential address: aerobiology — science in progress]</ref> From 1952-1964, he was director of their Systematisch-Geobotanisches Institut.<ref>[http://www.uni-goettingen.de/en/71395.html Georg-August-Universität Göttingen - Plant ecology and ecosystems research]</ref> Former students include [[Gerhard Lang]] and [[Heinz Ellenberg]].
==Education== Firbas studied at the German branch of [[Charles University]] (German Charles-Ferdinand University) under Prof. K. Rudolph. He was an assistant professor for a short time, before leaving to go to Germany.<ref>[http://www.preslia.cz/P123Krahulec.pdf History of the studies on the flora and vegetation in the Czech Republic]</ref>
