[[File:Nigerian National Parks.svg|thumb|300px|National Parks of Nigeria]] There are several '''national parks of Nigeria'''. The Nigeria National Park Service (NNPS) is responsible for preserving, enhancing, protecting and managing vegetation and wild animals in the national parks of [[Nigeria]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://nigeriaparkservice.org/functions.aspx |title=Functions |publisher=Nigeria National Park Service |accessdate=2010-10-21}}</ref> The NNPS is a parastatal under the Federal Ministry of the Environment, and is headed by a Conservator General.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://allafrica.com/stories/200910300153.html |title=National Parks Governing Board Inaugurated |work=Daily Trust |author=Mustapha Suleiman |date=29 October 2009 |accessdate=2010-10-21}}</ref> It works closely with the Nigerian Tourism Development Corporation.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tribune.com.ng/index.php/tourism/10738-npc-reaffirms-partnership-with-ntdc |title=NPC reaffirms partnership with NTDC |work=Nigerian Tribune |author=Wale Olapade |date=8 September 2010 |accessdate=2010-10-21}}</ref>
The first national park was [[Kainji National Park|Kainji Lake]], established by the military ruler General [[Olusegun Obasanjo]] in 1979. The National Parks Governing Board and five new National Parks were set up in 1991.
Yankari Game Reserve was upgraded to a national park in 1992, although it was later handed over to the Bauchi State government in June 2006.
The parks cover a total land area of approximately 20,156&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup>, or about 3% of Nigeria's total land area.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://nigeriaparkservice.org/evolution.aspx |title=Evolution of Parks in Nigeria |publisher=Nigeria National Park Service |accessdate=2010-10-21}}</ref>
==Parks== {|class="wikitable sortable" |- !style="width:8em;"|Park !! Area km<sup>2</sup> !! Established !! State(s) !! Notes |- |[[Chad Basin National Park|Chad Basin]] ||style="text-align:right"| 2,258 || 1991 || [[Borno State|Borno]], [[Yobe State|Yobe]] || Includes part of the [[Hadejia-Nguru wetlands]] and the [[Sambisa Game Reserve]] |- |[[Cross River National Park|Cross River]] ||style="text-align:right"| 4,000 || 1991 || [[Cross River State|Cross River]] || Okwangwo section and Oban section (1,906&nbsp;km²) |- |[[Gashaka Gumti National Park|Gashaka Gumti]] ||style="text-align:right"| 6,731 || 1991 || [[Taraba State|Taraba]], [[Adamawa State|Adamawa]] || |- |[[Kainji National Park|Kainji]] ||style="text-align:right"| 5,382 || 1979 || [[Niger State|Niger]], [[Kwara State|Kwara]] || Includes [[Kainji Lake]], [[Borgu Game Reserve]] and [[Zugurma Game Reserve]] |- |[[Kamuku National Park|Kamuku]] ||style="text-align:right"| 1,121 || 1999 || [[Kaduna State|Kaduna]] || |- |[[Okomu National Park|Okomu]] ||style="text-align:right"| 181 || 1999 || [[Edo State|Edo]] || Part of the [[Okomu Forest Reserve]] |- |[[Old Oyo National Park|Old Oyo]] ||style="text-align:right"| 2,512 || 1991 || [[Oyo State|Oyo]], [[Kwara State|Kwara]] || |- |[[Yankari National Park|Yankari]] ||style="text-align:right"| 2,244 || 1962 || [[Bauchi State|Bauchi]] || Operated by the Bauchi State government |}
