{{Infobox scientist | name = Vicentino Prestes de Almeida | image = | image_size = 175px | caption = | birth_date = 1900 | birth_place = [[Chiniquá]], [[São Pedro do Sul, Rio Grande do Sul|São Pedro do Sul]] | death_date = {{death date|1954|10|28}} | death_place = [[São Pedro do Sul, Rio Grande do Sul|São Pedro do Sul]] | residence = | citizenship = | nationality = [[Brazil]]ian | ethnicity = | field = [[paleontologist]] | work_institution = | alma_mater = | doctoral_advisor = | doctoral_students = | known_for = | author_abbreviation_bot = | author_abbreviation_zoo = | prizes = | religion = | footnotes = }}
'''''Vicentino Prestes de Almeida''''', (Born 1900 in [[Chiniquá]], [[Rio Grande do Sul]], [[Brazil]]) was a Brazilian [[paleontologist]]. He died on October 28, 1954, in [[São Pedro do Sul, Rio Grande do Sul|São Pedro do Sul]].
== Biography==
Prestes was a self-taught [[paleontologist]]. Beginning in 1925, he worked with many visiting [[paleontologist]]s in both [[Santa Maria, Rio Grande do Sul|Santa Maria]] and [[São Pedro do Sul, Rio Grande do Sul|São Pedro do Sul]] in the Brazilian state of Rio Grande do Sul.
Many of the fossils collected by Prestes are in [[museum]]s in [[Porto Alegre]], such as the [[Júlio de Castilhos Museum]], the [[Museu de Ciências Naturais da Fundação Zoobotânica do Rio Grande do Sul|Zoobotanical Natural History Museum of Rio Grande do Sul]], the [[Museum of Science and Technology (PUCRS)]] and the [[Institute of Geosciences of the Universidade Federal do Rio Grande do Sul#Museum of Paleontology Irajá Damiani Pinto|Museum of Paleontology Irajá Damiani Pinto]].
[[Friedrich von Huene]] named the carnivorous [[Triassic]] reptile [[Prestosuchus|Prestosuchus chiniquensis]] in Prestes's honor (from Prestes and Chiniquá, his birthplace).<ref>von Huene, Friedrich (1942) "Lieferungen 3/4. Pseudosuchia, Saurischia, Rhynchosauridae und Schlussabschnitt" ("Parts 3/4. Pseudosuchia, Saurischia, Rhynchosauridae, and Conclusions") ''Die Fossilen Reptilien des Südamerikanischen Gondwanalandes: Ergebnisse der Sauriergrabungen in Südbrasilien 1928/29'' (''The Fossil Reptiles of South American Gondwanaland: Results of the Dinosaur Expeditions in southern Brazil 1928/29'') C. H. Beck, Munich, Germany, pp. 161&ndash;332, {{OCLC|72550227}}</ref><ref>Couto, Carlos de Paula (1944) "Repteis e mamiferos fosseis do Brasil" An. IX. Congr. Brasil. Geogr., 8, 167—206, 15 Abb., Rio de Janeiro</ref>
Prestes organized and arranged the fossils for the Instituto de Educação General Flores da Cunha<ref>[http://www.aredencao.com.br/instituto.htm "Parque Farroupilha (Redenção): Instituto de Educação General Flores da Cunha"] in Portuguese; archived at [https://www.webcitation.org/664E3faFx https://www.webcitation.org/664E3faFx] by [[WebCite]]</ref> and contributed considerably to the Paleorrota Geopark.
